        'about.kicker': 'About TrackYourGains',
        'about.title': 'Your smart companion for training, nutrition & progress',
        'about.subtitle': 'TrackYourGains is a lean, locally running app that helps you keep an eye on your workouts, weight, and nutrition — no account, no cloud, 100% your thing.',
        'about.why.title': '💡 Why TrackYourGains?',
        'about.why.text1': 'I wanted a tool that is not overloaded, does not annoy you with paywalls, and still feels like a modern dashboard. An app you open and instantly see: Where am I right now?',
        'about.why.text2': 'TrackYourGains focuses on what matters: training, nutrition, progress — no bullshit, no data selling, and no hidden subscriptions.',
        'about.features.title': '🚀 What the app can already do',
        'about.features.item1': 'Plan workouts, document them & save them as plans',
        'about.features.item2': 'Weight tracking with history & statistics',
        'about.features.item3': 'Calorie and macro calculators (BMI, calorie needs, protein & more)',
        'about.features.item4': 'Training progress per plan as a journal view',
        'about.features.item5': 'Export options for your data (e.g. CSV / JSON depending on the area)',
        'about.features.note': 'Everything currently runs locally in your browser via LocalStorage. Your data belongs to you.',
        'about.focus.title': '🎯 App focus',
        'about.focus.text1': 'TrackYourGains is not a social fitness platform, but a tool. You compare yourself with yourself — not with influencers or random benchmarks.',
        'about.focus.text2': 'That is why the design intentionally feels like a personal dashboard: clear cards, readable statistics, and a dark, eye-friendly layout.',
        'about.privacy.title': '🔒 Privacy & transparency',
        'about.privacy.item1': 'No registration, no accounts',
        'about.privacy.item2': 'No server database — everything runs locally in your browser',
        'about.privacy.item3': 'You decide yourself whether and what you export',
        'about.privacy.item4': 'No tracking pixel, no analytics spam inside the app',
        'about.privacy.note': 'Optional cloud backups may be added later — but only if they are transparent, switchable, and easy to understand.',
        'about.me.title': '👨‍💻 Who is behind it?',
        'about.me.text1': 'Hey, I am Justin — fitness nerd, tech fan, and the person building TrackYourGains.',
        'about.me.text2': 'The idea came from a simple problem: too many apps wanted my data, my money, or overloaded me with features I never needed. So I started building my own tool.',
        'about.me.text3': 'My goal: an app that feels like a well-designed training plan — clearly structured, focused, and without unnecessary clutter.',
        'about.me.text4': 'I keep working on the website and the app, test new ideas, and improve what is already there. At the same time, I am working on a fair, optional subscription model so I can keep expanding TrackYourGains long-term.',
        'about.me.feedback': 'If you have feedback, ideas, or criticism: just message me through the contact page.',
        'about.roadmap.title': '🛠️ Planned features',
        'about.roadmap.item1': 'More analysis for individual exercises (e.g. 1RM history)',
        'about.roadmap.item2': 'Optional training goals with reminders',
        'about.roadmap.item3': 'More export formats for coaches & physios',
        'about.roadmap.item4': 'Improved mobile experience & small UI tweaks',
        'about.roadmap.item5': 'optional Pro subscription for more features',
        'about.roadmap.note': 'The roadmap is alive: I adapt it based on what users actually need — not what just sounds fancy.',
        'about.help.title': '💬 How you can help',
        'about.help.item1': 'Send me bugs, screenshots, or weird edge cases',
        'about.help.item2': 'Tell me how you use TrackYourGains in everyday life',
        'about.help.item3': 'Be honest about what is annoying — design, UX, texts, anything',
        'about.help.note': 'Your feedback flows directly into the next update. The more honest you are, the better this thing gets.',
        'about.footer.title': '📈 Your progress, your rules',
        'about.footer.text': 'TrackYourGains should help you stay consistent long-term — without outside pressure, without gamification stress. Open the dashboard, see your progress, and decide yourself what the next useful step is.',
        'about.footer.cta': 'Go to progress dashboard',
